President Trump gave a speech at Tampa Bay Technical High School in Florida, where he discussed the importance of vocational education and the current state of the economy. He mentioned the growth in GDP, the reduction in trade deficit, and the creation of 3.7 million new jobs since the election. He also highlighted the National Council for the American Worker and the "Our Pledge to American Workers" campaign, which aims to train and retrain over 4 million American students and workers. The President signed the Perkins Career and Technical Education Act into law and praised the success stories of graduates from Tampa Bay Tech. He emphasized the importance of investing in workers and building the American Dream.